🛒 E-Commerce Data Analysis Project
🔍 Overview

This project analyzes a multi-table e-commerce dataset to extract business insights related to sales performance, 
customer behavior, and product trends. The analysis was performed using SQL for data exploration and Power BI 
for interactive visualization.

🛠️ Tools Used
MySQL (Data Analysis, Joins, Aggregations, Window Functions)
Power BI (Data Modeling & Dashboard)
Excel (Initial inspection)

🗂️ Dataset Description
The dataset consists of multiple related tables:

orders → transaction-level data (order value, category, date, delivery status)
customers → customer demographics (age, gender, city, loyalty score)
products → product details (name, category, price, stock)
reviews → customer reviews and ratings
🔗 Data Modeling

Relationships created:

orders.customer_id → customers.customer_id
reviews.customer_id → customers.customer_id
reviews.product_id → products.product_id

This enabled multi-dimensional analysis across customers, products, and transactions.

🧠 Problem Statement
The goal was to answer key business questions:

Which categories generate the most revenue?
Which cities contribute the most sales?
Who are the most valuable customers?
How do customer segments behave?
How do product ratings vary across categories?

🛠️ Approach
Performed SQL joins across multiple tables
Aggregated revenue and customer metrics
Applied customer segmentation using loyalty score
Analyzed product performance and review ratings
Built a Power BI dashboard for interactive insights

📊 Key Insights
⚡ Top Category: Electronics generated the highest revenue
🌆 Top City: Mumbai contributed the most to total sales
👥 Customer Segmentation: Majority of customers fall into the low-to-medium value segment
📈 Sales Trend: Revenue fluctuates monthly with noticeable peaks during mid-year
⭐ Product Feedback: Some categories show higher average ratings, indicating better customer satisfaction

📊 Dashboard Features
KPI Cards (Total Revenue, Total Orders, Average Order Value)
Revenue by Category
Revenue by City
Monthly Revenue Trend
Customer Segmentation (High / Medium / Low Value)
Product Rating Analysis
Interactive Filters (City, Category, Gender, Delivery Status)

🧠 SQL Analysis
Performed advanced SQL queries, including:

Revenue aggregation by category and city
Customer-level spending analysis
Average order value (AOV)
Customer segmentation using CASE statements
Monthly trend analysis
Multi-table joins for deeper insights

📁 Files Included
synthetic_ecommerce_dataset_multisheet.csv / tables → Dataset
EDA_on_ecommerce_data.sql → SQL queries
Ecommerce Dashboard.pbix
Ecommerce Dashboard.png → Dashboard screenshot

🚀 Conclusion
This project demonstrates the ability to work with relational datasets, perform advanced SQL analysis, 
and build business intelligence dashboards. It highlights skills in data modeling, customer analysis, and insight generation.
